## Code Quality and Best Practices
- write self-documenting code with clear variable and function names
- implement proper TypeScript types for all data structures
- use strict TypeScript configuration
- implement proper error handling with try-catch blocks
- use meaningful commit messages with conventional commits
- avoid writing useless comments
- use consistent code formatting and style
- implement proper unit tests for critical functions
- use dependency injection when appropriate
- implement proper separation of concerns
- use design patterns appropriately (DRY, SOLID principles)
- implement proper input validation and sanitization
- use proper async/await patterns instead of callbacks
- implement proper memory management and cleanup
- use proper error boundaries and fallback UI